    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <add>ד"ה יום א' י"ד מרחשון תרי"ב לה"ק</add>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revr Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p>if it is possible for you to but the writings of <persName>Mrs<lb/> Levy</persName>
                is your Paper you would oblige much me<lb/> by so doing, as I think also it would be
                probably<lb/> Interesting for your Paper, or if you can't but<lb/> the whole in, at
                least, some <sic>coments</sic></p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I remain you Respecfy</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">A Lowenstrit</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Cleveland</placeName>
                <date>Novbr 11<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1887</date>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>With the Help of God.</p>
            <p><date><sic>tuesday</sic>, October 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date>
                <add>?</add><lb/> the year <date>5612</date> according our calculation</p>
            <p>Peace &amp; happiness to my<lb/> friend the dear and respectable<lb/> man the great
                scholar<lb/> the pious man who is<lb/> known <del>all</del> over all the
                congregations<lb/> that are reassured all<lb/> over the <placeName>United
                    States</placeName>.<lb/> and famous for your notriety<add>?</add><lb/>
                <persName>Rev. Isaack <sic>Lesser</sic></persName>.</p>
            <p>Being in distress I am<lb/> applying to you, <del>my</del> your<lb/> honor or your
                name is<lb/> known to everyone as a<lb/> honest and <del>right</del>
                <sic>truthfull</sic><lb/> man.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">II</p>
            <p>I recd my copy which is<lb/>
                <sic>inclosed</sic> in this letter and<lb/> to criticize it thank to your<lb/>
                <del>long</del> great knowledge and to give<lb/> your opinion and trial<lb/> between
                me and my opponent<lb/> who is righteous<lb/> and how wise and <sic>plesant</sic>
                it<lb/> would be if your honor<lb/> will approve it grant me this copy<lb/> to be
                written <del>published</del> in original<lb/> Hebrew. My journal will be<lb/> a
                monthly <del>one</del> edition and would<lb/> be called “Occident.”<lb/> According
                my <sic>opinien</sic><lb/> it is a <add>שלום וכל טוב לידיד ה' האיש הנכבד והיקר
                    והנבון והמשכיל ירא ה' נודע בשערים</add> to publish<lb/> and <sic>advertize</sic>
                among<lb/> all the Hebrew that live<lb/> in <placeName>U. S.</placeName></p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">III</p>
            <p>and to save them from<lb/> low habits.</p>
            <p>You shall reward with<lb/> kindness find and<lb/> honest people and you shall<lb/>
                live long and succeed<lb/> in all your life's affairs<lb/> according my
                    <sic>heartly</sic><lb/> wish your friend<lb/> who bends his head down<lb/>
                <add>בכל קהלות מדינות אמעריקא לשם ולתהלה מו"ה יצחק לידער נרי יאיר לנצח!</add><lb/>
                <persName>Joseph</persName> the son of <persName>Isaac</persName><lb/>
                <del>who</del>
                <persName>Levy</persName>. Who resides<lb/> in the Holy Community<lb/> the men of
                Mercy at<lb/>
                <placeName>Cleveland</placeName>.</p>
        </body>
